<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-04T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-04T06:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">362.1154 Spiegelberg, Betty G./7:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-04T12:00:00+01:00">September 4, 1936—12
                                    noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 4—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>272. Department’s 114, September 3, 2 p.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d211fn3">Not printed.</note> On the basis of a definite negative decision
                            received from the Foreign Office September 2 a complete report on the
                            Spiegelberg case<note n="3" xml:id="d211fn4">Not printed.</note> being
                            forwarded by pouch on the <hi rend="italic">Europa</hi> sailing
                            September 5. Suggest no further action until it is received.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dodd</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>